CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 15, 1947, pg. 4, reads: "Receive Bachelor's Degree - George Greenlee Jr. received they degree of Bachelor of Science from the School of Pharmacy, University of Pittsburgh, last Wednesday morning at the commencement exercises held at Soldier's and Sailor's Memorial Hall. He shakes hands with John Gobble who received the degree of Bachelor of Arts. Mr. Gobble majored in history. He plans to do graduate work in the future. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: University of Pittsburgh graduated George Greenlee Jr. and John Gobble shaking hands at commencement ceremonies, Soldier's and Sailors Memorial Hall
